{"id": "1116", "instruction": "What are the points of inflection of the graph of $f(x) = \\frac{ x+1 }{ x^2+1 }$?\n\nOptions:\nA. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{3}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{3}\nB. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{8}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{8}\nC. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{10}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{10}\nD. x_1=1, x_2=-1+\\sqrt{3}, x_3=-1-\\sqrt{3}\nE. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{4}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{4}\nF. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{6}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{6}\nG. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{7}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{7}\nH. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{2}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{2}\nI. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{5}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{5}\nJ. x_1=1, x_2=-2+\\sqrt{1}, x_3=-2-\\sqrt{1}", "output": "A"}
